SOP-Installing a Self-hosted RAG Server on Rocky Linux 9.7 with user

SOP: Installing a Self-Hosted RAG Server on Rocky Linux 9.7 (User: user1)
Stack: Milvus Vector DB, Hugging Face embeddings, LlamaIndex, and FastAPI.
Step 1: Update System & Install Dependencies
Run these with sudo to manage system packages:
Bash
sudo dnf update -y
sudo dnf install -y dnf-plugins-core gcc gcc-c++ make
Step 2: Install Docker Engine + Docker Compose
Clean out old versions and install the official Docker engine.
Bash
# Remove old versions
sudo dnf remove -y docker docker-client docker-client-latest docker-common \
docker-latest docker-latest-logrotate docker-logrotate docker-engine

# Add Docker repo and install
sudo dnf config-manager --add-repo https://download.docker.com/linux/centos/docker-ce.repo
sudo dnf install -y docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io docker-buildx-plugin docker-compose-plugin

# Start & enable services
sudo systemctl enable --now docker

# Add 'user1' to docker group (Crucial: log out and back in after this)
sudo usermod -aG docker user1
Step 3: Install & Start Milvus Standalone (v2.6.12)
As the user user1, create the directory in your home folder.
Bash
mkdir -p ~/milvus && cd ~/milvus
wget https://github.com/milvus-io/milvus/releases/download/v2.6.12/milvus-standalone-docker-compose.yml -O docker-compose.yml

# Start containers (as user1, thanks to the group addition above)
docker compose up -d
•	Verify: docker compose ps.
•	Data Path: /home/user1/milvus/volumes/.
Step 4: Install Python 3.11
Bash
sudo dnf install -y python3.11 python3.11-pip python3.11-devel
Step 5: Create Project & Virtual Environment
Set up the environment within user1's home directory.
Bash
mkdir -p ~/rag-server/data && cd ~/rag-server
python3.11 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
pip install --upgrade pip setuptools wheel
Step 6: Install Python Packages
Install the LlamaIndex and FastAPI stack.
Bash
pip install llama-index llama-index-vector-stores-milvus llama-index-embeddings-huggingface llama-index-llms-huggingface fastapi uvicorn pydantic
# CPU-only Torch
pip install torch torchvision torchaudio --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cpu
Step 7: Create the RAG Index
Create setup_index.py in ~/rag-server/. Ensure the Milvus URI points to localhost.
Python
from llama_index.core import Settings, VectorStoreIndex, StorageContext, SimpleDirectoryReader
from llama_index.embeddings.huggingface import HuggingFaceEmbedding
from llama_index.vector_stores.milvus import MilvusVectorStore

Settings.embed_model = HuggingFaceEmbedding(model_name="BAAI/bge-small-en-v1.5")

vector_store = MilvusVectorStore(
    uri="http://localhost:19530",
    dim=384,
    collection_name="rag_collection",
    overwrite=True
)
storage_context = StorageContext.from_defaults(vector_store=vector_store)
documents = SimpleDirectoryReader("data").load_data()
index = VectorStoreIndex.from_documents(documents, storage_context=storage_context)
print("RAG index created successfully!")
Run it: python setup_index.py. Place your documents in /home/user1/rag-server/data/.
Step 8: Build the RAG Server (FastAPI)
Create app.py in ~/rag-server/. This will serve the API on port 8000.
Step 9: Run and Test
Start the server manually to verify it works:
Bash
uvicorn app:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 --reload
Test using the new hostname:
Bash
curl -X POST http://rag-server:8000/query -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"query": "What is the main topic?"}'
Step 10: Run as System Service (Production)
Create the service file using sudo. Note the updated paths for 'user1':
Ini, TOML
[Unit]
Description=RAG Server
After=network.target docker.service

[Service]
User=user1
WorkingDirectory=/home/user1/rag-server
Environment="PATH=/home/user1/rag-server/venv/bin"
ExecStart=/home/user1/rag-server/venv/bin/uvicorn app:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
Restart=always

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
Activate:
Bash
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable --now rag-server

